# 2026-04-08-ghost



## G is for Ghost

I was convinced my parents old house was haunted. It was built in the early 1900s, had faded and peeling wallpaper. Dilapidation
and general neglect for the past eighty or so years was abundant. But what made me think it was haunted was the mirrors. My mom
told me when we first moved in, when I was four, that the mirrors were placed the way they were because it was easier to see the
back of your head when giving yourself a haircut. But every bathroom had infinity mirrors, due to not just ONE mirror in front and
one behind, but one the left. Meaning if you angle the front mirror you get the rare, diagonal infinity fun house mirror effect.

I can't tell you how weird it was, every time I brushed my teeth. I would just feel the infinity to my left and front and behind.
Which again, by itself wasn't bad, but with the addition of the mealy falling apart stucco shamrock colored wall next to the shower.
Would just freak me out.

I do have stories associated with those mirrors, and I did play Bloody Mary with them, because everyones a teen a once. But yeah,
thanks for letting me share.


